##"Am I coming down with a new pneumonia? " You ask

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

By Keith Chen, _ thepaper_news _

"'am I suffering from new coronary pneumonia? ' This is the most frequently seen question in online consultations, " Liu Fei, a psychiatrist at Shanghai's Tongji Hospital, told The Paper news on Feb. 17.

These days, Tongji Hospital has received a large number of online and offline help and consultation, such as the Internet, telephone and outpatient services. Some people have insomnia due to the epidemic, and some patients with anxiety disorder who have been emotionally stable have experienced mood swings again. The number of the epidemic continues to rise affecting the people, the outbreak of fear, panic, anxiety, how to solve?

Don't hold your phone in your hand

Liu Fei pointed out that a recent survey showed that nearly 80 percent of the people were very concerned about the progress of the epidemic. Only a few of them remained optimistic. Most of them had strong worries and fears, and there was no lack of people who thought they were likely to be infected with "new crown" pneumonia.

In this regard, he believed that with the outbreak of the new coronavirus epidemic, citizens began to "stay at home" mode, and news of the epidemic became the focus of daily life. Regardless of whether it is true or not, most citizens chose to believe it, and then pay too much attention to the epidemic. "since most of the cases of NCP are not serious and are not particularly obvious, many citizens begin to doubt whether they are infected due to occasional dry cough, sneezing and sore throat. "

Is this even normal? Liu Fei explained that in fact, psychology believes that fear and anxiety in the face of disaster is a normal stress reaction, which can lead to heart palpitations, shortness of breath, irritability, restlessness, physical discomfort and even emotional loss. A simple way to identify this is to first look around to see if there are more specific causes of discomfort, such as lack of air circulation or drinking water, and then think about how much attention you are paying to something, if there were any obvious signs of discomfort, and concluded that I was being overly anxious.

Earlier, experts at the Chinese Academy of Sciences also issued public recommendations: to stabilize the mood, carefully observe whether the symptoms and new crown pneumonia is consistent, the body does not feel normal to see a doctor; control behavior, divert attention, there is a "hypochondriac state" to be taken seriously, you can ask for help.

In addition to on-line consultation, off-line clinic, Liu Fei also recently found that there are many dispensing patients mentioned that sleep problems, although many patients answered no. But deep into its cause will find that the main cause of insomnia patients is the new pneumonia outbreak, can not go out, lying screen time longer, disturbed sleep patterns.

"In this case, we suggest that there is no need to take the drug immediately or rush to increase the dose of the original sleep-improving drug, but rather that lifestyle changes and changes should be given priority. When we don't go out, we should control the hand, don't always hold the phone, must control the screen time."

Liu Fei further said that recently many patients with mild new coronary pneumonia in the Wuhan square-cabin hospital are role models. Facing the fact that they are suffering from new coronary pneumonia, they choose to respond with an optimistic and positive state, such as spontaneously organizing square dancing, borrow books to study, and some talk about love, and even in the shelter of both parents have met.

Families need to increase their support for the elderly

Liu Fei also mentioned that in addition to sleep problems, there are also a number of patients with anxiety disorders and depression in the outpatient clinic, and their mood swings are higher, "For example, an elderly woman with an anxiety disorder who had been cured with systematic treatment and remained emotionally stable for nearly a decade without medication experienced stress and anxiety a week ago due to fear of viral infection. There are also patients who have had to be treated again after they stopped taking their medication because they had the common cold during the outbreak and were overly worried, causing anxiety and difficulty in regulating themselves."

"In special periods, we will take individual adjustment as the principle, attach importance to humanistic and environmental factors, attach importance to psychological adjustment, discuss life style adjustment. Not all patients with anxiety and depression will increase the dosage or start taking medicine again. "

Liu Fei, for example, said he met an elderly patient with depression during his treatment who had taken sufficient doses of two antidepressants and was in a period of emotional stability. Recently, he had a bad mood and was pessimistic, that the outbreak is getting worse and there's no hope. Ask The reason, only to find that is accompanied by her nanny because of isolation in the home, unable to return to Shanghai, loneliness led to their illness fluctuations.

"At this time, the key to solving the problem is to increase the company of family members such as children and to eliminate their loneliness, " Liu explained.

At present, whether for first or second visits, people often have such doubts. In case they go to the hospital to see a doctor, it would be unfortunate if they are infected without being ill. In particular, quite a number of patients have learned that they have already been diagnosed at the hospital in which they were treated, just procrastinate or stop taking your medication.

Liu suggested that any delay or interruption of its own treatment would be undesirable. The situation is serious, and it is normal to have worries and doubts, but scientific protection is the absolute truth. Worrying can not solve any problems, but will cause adverse consequences. As an individual, we should bear in mind the precautionary principle and raise the level of protection. Since the outbreak, major hospitals have launched contingency plans to minimize the risk of nosocomial transmission of the virus.

"Taking Tongji Hospital in Shanghai as an example, from the temperature screening when entering the hospital, to outpatient flow restriction, to disinfection and epidemic prevention, every link is to ensure the safety of patients and medical staff. We must be confident, scientific prevention and control, accurate treatment, we will eventually overcome the epidemic, timely medical treatment, emotional problems will be resolved as soon as possible,"Liu said.

This issue is edited by Yu Hua Zhou
